---
// Who Wrote These Rules?
---

<section class="py-16 md:py-24 bg-white">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-12">
    <div class="section-line bg-red-500 mb-6"></div>
    <h2 class="font-display font-extrabold text-3xl md:text-4xl tracking-tight mb-3">
      Who Wrote These Rules?
    </h2>
    <p class="font-body text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mb-10">
      The tax code didn't write itself. Every loophole, every exemption, every special provision was put there by someone. Here's who.
    </p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-8">
      <div class="card p-6 text-center">
        <div class="stat-large text-red-600">$4.4B</div>
        <div class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mt-2">Lobbying (2024)</div>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mt-2">Spent influencing Congress</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="card p-6 text-center">
        <div class="stat-large text-red-600">$1.9B</div>
        <div class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mt-2">Dark Money</div>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mt-2">Untraceable political spending</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="card p-6 text-center">
        <div class="stat-large text-red-600">$15.7B</div>
        <div class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mt-2">PAC Activity</div>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mt-2">2024 election cycle</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Both Parties -->
    <div class="card p-6">
      <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-gray-900 mb-4 text-center">
        Here's the Thing About "Both Sides"
      </h3>

      <div class="mb-6">
        <img
          src="/who-makes-the-rules.png"
          alt="Politicians from both parties shaking hands, covered in corporate sponsor patches"
          class="w-full max-w-2xl mx-auto rounded-xl shadow-lg"
        />
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
        <div class="bg-blue-50 p-4 rounded-xl">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-blue-800 mb-2">Top Democratic Donors</h4>
          <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
            <li>• Finance & Insurance</li>
            <li>• Tech Giants</li>
            <li>• Healthcare Industry</li>
            <li>• Real Estate</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-red-50 p-4 rounded-xl">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-800 mb-2">Top Republican Donors</h4>
          <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
            <li>• Finance & Insurance</li>
            <li>• Tech Giants</li>
            <li>• Healthcare Industry</li>
            <li>• Real Estate</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <p class="font-body text-lg text-gray-700 text-center">
        Notice anything? <strong>The same industries fund both parties.</strong> They don't care who wins. They win either way.
      </p>
      
      <p class="font-mono text-sm text-gray-400 mt-4 text-center">
        OpenSecrets / Brennan Center for Justice, 2024
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
